brcdDot1xAuth.name: brcdDot1xAuth

brcdDot1xAuth.description: Management Information for configuration /querying of 802.1x authentication It is grouped into five MIBs - 1. Global level configurable admin /status 802.1x information 2. Port level EAPOL statistics information 3. Port level configuration information 4. Different Port state information and 5. 802.1x mac session information Copyright 1996-2010 Brocade Communications Systems, Inc. All rights reserved. VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigQuietperiod.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigQuietperiod
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigQuietperiod.description: When the Brocade device is unable to authenticate a Client, the amount of time the Brocade device waits before trying again.. The allowed range is from 1 to 4294967294

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigTxPeriod.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigTxPeriod
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigTxPeriod.description: When a Client does not send back an EAP(Extensible Authentication Protocol)-response/identity frame, the amount of time the Brocade device waits before retransmitting the EAP-request/identity frame to a Client The allowed range is from 1 to 4294967294

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigSuppTimeOut.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigSuppTimeOut
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigSuppTimeOut.description: When a supplicant (Client) does not respond to an EAP-request frame, the amount of time before the Brocade device retransmits the frame The allowed range is from 1 to 4294967294

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigAuthServerTimeO.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigAuthServerTimeOut
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigAuthServerTimeO.description: When the Authentication Server (RADIUS) does not respond to a message sent from the Client, the amount of time before the Brocade device retransmits the message. The allowed range is from 1 to 4294967294

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigMaxReq.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigMaxReq
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigMaxReq.description: The number of times the Brocade device retransmits an EAP-request/identity request frame if it does not receive an EAP-response/identity response frame from a Client

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReAuthMax.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReAuthMax
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReAuthMax.description: The number of re-authentication attempts that are permitted before the port becomes Unauthorized

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReAuthPeriod.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReAuthPeriod
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReAuthPeriod.description: How often the device automatically re-authenticates clients when periodic re-authentication is enabled The allowed range is from 1 to 4294967294

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigTotalPortsEnabl.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigTotalPortsEnabled
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigTotalPortsEnabl.description: The total number of ports that have 802.1x enabled

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReauthStatus.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReauthStatus
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigReauthStatus.description: Used to enable / disable Reauthentication globally

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigMacSessionMaxAg.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigMacSessionMaxAge
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigMacSessionMaxAg.description: The Max-Age of the 802.1x mac session- A value between 0 and 65535

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigNoAgingDeniedSe.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigNoAgingDeniedSessions
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigNoAgingDeniedSe.description: Enable / Disable Mac-Session-No Aging for Denied sessions

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigNoAgingPermitte.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigNoAgingPermittedSessions
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigNoAgingPermitte.description: Enable / Disable Mac-Session-No Aging for Permitted sessions

brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigAuthFailAction.name: brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigAuthFailAction
brcdDot1xAuthGlobalConfigAuthFailAction.description: To Configure the action to take when the authentication fails

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTable.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTable
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTable.description: A table that contains port EAP(Extensible Authentication Protocol) frames statistics for 802.1x authentication

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatEntry.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatEntry
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatEntry.description: An entry of EAP frames statistics indexed by ifIndex

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPFrames.description: The total number of EAPOL frames received on the port It includes EAP frames -

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxEAPFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxEAPFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxEAPFrames.description: The no of EAPOL frames transmitted on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPStartFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPStartFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPStartFrames.description: The number of EAPOL-Start frames received on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPLogOffFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPLogOffFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPLogOffFrames.description: The number of EAPOL-Logoff frames received on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPRespIdFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPRespIdFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPRespIdFrames.description: The number of EAP frames other than Response/Identity frames received on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxEAPReqIdFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxEAPReqIdFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxEAPReqIdFrames.description: The number of EAP-Request/Identity frames transmitted on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPInvalidFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPInvalidFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPInvalidFrames.description: The number of invalid EAPOL frames received on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatEAPLastFrameVersion.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatEAPLastFrameVersionRx
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatEAPLastFrameVersion.description: The version of last EAP frame received

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPRespOrIdFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPRespOrIdFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxEAPRespOrIdFrames.description: The number of received EAP response or Id frames on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxLengthErrorFrame.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxLengthErrorFrame
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatRxLengthErrorFrame.description: The received EAP Length Error frame

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxRequestFrames.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxRequestFrames
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatTxRequestFrames.description: The number of transmitted EAP request frames on the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatLastEAPFrameSource.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatLastEAPFrameSource
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatLastEAPFrameSource.description: The MAC address of the source from which the last EAP frame came

brcdDot1xAuthPortStateTable.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStateTable
brcdDot1xAuthPortStateTable.description: A table that contains entries of port dot1x values

brcdDot1xAuthPortStateEntry.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStateEntry
brcdDot1xAuthPortStateEntry.description: An entry of 802.1x config values indexed by ifIndex to be able to have port values

brcdDot1xAuthPortStateMacSessions.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStateMacSessions
brcdDot1xAuthPortStateMacSessions.description: Number of 802.1x MAC sessions per port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStateAuthMacSessions.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStateAuthMacSessions
brcdDot1xAuthPortStateAuthMacSessions.description: Number of Authorized MAC sessions per port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStateOriginalPVID.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStateOriginalPVID
brcdDot1xAuthPortStateOriginalPVID.description: Originally configured(not dynamically assigned) PVID(port's default VLAN ID) for the port

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVIDMacTotal.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVIDMacTotal
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVIDMacTotal.description: The number of devices transmitting untagged traffic on the port's PVID

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVIDMacAuthorized.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVIDMacAuthorized
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVIDMacAuthorized.description: The number of devices transmitting untagged traffic on the port's PVID as a result of dynamic VLAN assignment

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePortVlanState.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePortVlanState
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePortVlanState.description: The Current Vlan state the port is in, which can be RADIUS -The port's PVID was dynamically assigned by a RADIUS server Restricted - The port's PVID is the restricted VLAN Normal - The port's PVID is not set by a RADIUS server, nor is it the restricted VLAN

brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVID.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVID
brcdDot1xAuthPortStatePVID.description: The Dot1x Authentication default Port VLAN Id

brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigTable.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigTable
brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigTable.description: A table that allows configuration of dot1x values for a given port

brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigPortControl.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigPortControl
brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigPortControl.description: The configured port control type for the interface which can be 1. force-unauthorized - port's controlled port is placed unconditionally in the unauthorized state 2. control-auto - the controlled port is unauthorized until authentication takes place between client and RADIUS 3. force-authorized - the port's controlled port is placed unconditionally in the authorized state

brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigFilterStrictSec.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigFilterStrictSec
brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigFilterStrictSec.description: To configure filter strict security on the interface - enable(1) or disable(0)

brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigDot1xOnPort.name: brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigDot1xOnPort
brcdDot1xAuthPortConfigDot1xOnPort.description: To Configure (enable / disable) 802.1x on an interface level

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionTable.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionTable
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionTable.description: A table that contains 802.1x MAC sessions

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionEntry.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionEntry
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular interface and client MAC ie., dot1x-mac-session

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAuthMac.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAuthMac
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAuthMac.description: Mac address of the client - which basically represents the username used for RADIUS authentication

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionUserName.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionUserName
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionUserName.description: User name of the 802.1x mac session

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionCurrentVlanId.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionCurrentVlanId
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionCurrentVlanId.description: The VLAN to which the port is currently assigned

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAccessStatus.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAccessStatus
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAccessStatus.description: The authentication state of the dot1x-mac-session - which can be permitted, denied, restricted or in the Init state

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionMaxAge.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionMaxAge
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionMaxAge.description: MAX Age of the mac session in which the MAC address is authenticated.

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAddrType.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAddrType
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAddrType.description: Client(supplicant) IP address Type. Supported address types are ipv4(1) and ipv6(2)

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionIpAddr.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionIpAddr
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionIpAddr.description: The IP Address of the client

brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAging.name: brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAging
brcdDot1xAuthMacSessionAging.description: The age's type - Hardware or Software aging, Ena in which case the aging hasn't started, or notapplicable when there is a fake 802.1x mac session
